        "text": "Here’s a neat, data-backed “rare-earth” (lanthanide) pattern: as you go from La to Lu, the overall stability of their 1:1 complexes with aminopolycarboxylate chelators increases. This captures the classic lanthanide contraction effect (decreasing ionic radius → higher charge density → stronger binding).",
