      {
        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "Why it’s interesting\n- The monotonic rise from La → Lu with a given ligand is a direct manifestation of lanthanide contraction and underpins many REE separation strategies: later lanthanides are preferentially complexed.\n- Comparing ligands shows how donor set/denticity shifts absolute strength while preserving the trend (HEDTA is ~2–3 log units weaker than EDTA for the examples above).\n- SRD-46 also lists extensive data for DTPA (ligand_6356; 300+ measurements), enabling even stronger complexes; the same La → Lu increase is observed for such higher-denticity chelators.",
